If there is a failure, the link is restarted by MTP-L3. This is a timer-controlled process that normally makes the link come back into service. If the link does not come back into service, check the configuration, physical connections and the hardware. 
Check physical connections and hardware as follows:  
*Check if there are broken cables.;
*Check if there are oxidized or loose connections.;
*Check if any fibre cables has a small bend radius less than the specified minimum bend radius. For example, ANSI/TIA/EIA 568 B  states a minimum bend radius of 10 to 20 times the outer cable diameter for intrabuilding backbone purposes, depending on load conditions. If the bend radius is too small, the cable can be broken or have limited functionality. Replace the cable.;

