This alarm is generated in one of the following situations: 
*Control system restarts (including small restart, large restart, initial start up, software upgrade, software update, and patching).; 
*During the restart of all SS7 devices.; 
*Blocked PIUs or VMs on which SS7 functionality is executed.;

This alarm is generated when there is no SS7 device available for SS7 signaling.
The reason for this may be as follows:
*SS7 configuration problem.;
*Internal software error or hardware failure.;
*Reboot of all PIUs or VMs executing SS7 functionality due to execution of the #activate_config_pending# CLI command.;
*Manually or automatically blocked PIUs or VMs.;

Allow a few minutes for the alarm to clear automatically. If the alarm remains, take the following actions:
*Check for hardware failures.;
*Unblock blocked PIUs or VMs by using the #deblock_eq# CLI command.;
*Check recent SS7 configuration changes.;
*Roll back to a known working software configuration.;
*Contact Ericsson support.;

