Auto negotiation has failed. This alarm will be issued if Auto-Negotiation is enabled and the peer device does not support any of the following capabilities:
*10BASE-T half or full duplex;
*100BASE-TXhalf or full duplex;
*1000BASE-T half or full duplex.;
This will probably only happen if the peer device only supports 100BASE-T4 and has Auto-Negotiation enabled. #Note: When the peer device does not have Auto-Negotiation enabled or does not support Auto-Negotiation at all and the Auto-Negotiation is enabled on the Line Card (LC) Ethernet port, the Parallel Detection mechanism can determine if the peer device is using 10BASE-T or 100BASE-TX but it can not determine if half duplex or full duplex is used. Note#

*Check that autonegotiation is enabled for all external interface ports, as well as for all equipment connected directly to node. For equipment connected directly to the node, use the get_eth_port CLI command to check if autonegotiation is enabled. If it is disabled, enable it using the modify_eth_port CLI command.;
