Alarm storm of a specific clear alarm in the SS7 back-end process:
*Storm of SS7 alarm <alarm name> (clear) has been detected. The alarm has been cleared and will be discarded for <number> seconds.;
Alarm storm in the SS7 back-end process:
*Storm of SS7 alarms has been detected. Some SS7 alarms will be discarded.;
Alarm storm in the SS7 O&M entity:
*Storm of SS7 alarm <alarm name> has been detected. The alarm has been cleared and deactivated for <number> seconds. <Number> alarms discarded before deactivation.;

The export can fail for any of the following reasons:
*The value of the AutoExportUri parameter is invalid.;
*The value of the AutoExportPassword parameter is invalid.;
*The SGSN-MME has failed to connect to the remote SFTP server.;

The alarm is cleared in the following cases:
*The configuration backup is successfully exported.;
*The automatic export of backups is disabled for the config backup manager.;
*The config backup manager is disabled.;

The alarm can be caused by the following:
*The TAI is not valid for the AMF.;
*The TAI is not configured in the AMF.;
*Faulty DNS configuration, which has caused the gNodeB to connect to the wrong AMF.;
#Note:The NgTrackingAreaValidation parameter has to be enabled for the TAC values to be checked.#Note:If more than one TA is received, the alarm is generated if any of the received TAs are invalid for the AMF.Note#
