The causes for this event are listed below. It can be one of them, or both.
*Incorrect data received from the RNC.;
*Incorrect data in the configuration tables;

An automatic reload of the SGSN-MME has occurred which has loaded one of the following SCs:
*The permanent (default) SC, if the reload is performed during startup.;
*The current SC in case of processing module failure or capsule failure.;

The event is generated when one of the following occurs:
*Frequent large restarts have escalated to a node restart.;
*A processing module failure or capsule failure has occurred that cannot be handled by a less extensive restart level.;

The event is generated when one of the following occurs:
*An operator has manually requested a small restart.;
*An error is detected in the software controlling all subscribers in the SGSN-MME.;
*An escalation from Small Local Restart to Small Restart.;

The consequences of this event are as follows:
*Stable subscribers are not affected.;
*Unstable subscribers are removed. Unstable subscribers are subscribers performing control signaling.;

The status of the pool move operation can be showed:
