The fsbBecomeMaster event indicates when an FSB has become primary. This is normal during node startup. The FsbId parameter indicates the FSB that becomes the primary and can have the following values:
*FSB-1: the event concerns the leftmost FSB;
*FSB-2: the event concerns the rightmost FSB;

The event is generated when a PIU takes the role of the active RP during any of the following scenarios:
*Node start-up;
*Start-up after software upgrade;
*RP failover;
*RP switchover;

This event is generated when the SGSN-MME is ready for traffic after a start or restart. The level of the completed restart is given.
The variable Restart Level can have the following values:
*Start;
*Small Local Restart;
*Small Restart;
*Large Restart;
*DP take over;
*AP take over;

The event is generated when one of the following occurs:
*The SGSN-MME has been started initially.;
*An operator has manually requested a restart.;
*An error has occurred and the SGSN-MME has triggered either a small local restart, small restart, large restart, or an AP/DP takeover.;
*An operator has blocked or deblocked a PIU or VM by using any of the #block_eq# or #deblock_eq# CLI commands.;

Perform the following actions:
*Stop the pool move operation.;
*Upgrade the specified target MME to 13B.;

The following are the most likely reasons for this event:
*The log's Min. Wrap Interval value is too high.;
*The log's Max. File Size value is too low.;
*The log's Number of Files value is too low.;

For the log, increase at least one of the following values by using the #set_log_config# CLI command:
*Max. File Size;
*Number of Files;
For the log, decrease the following value by using the #set_log_config# CLI command. 
*Min. Wrap Interval;
